<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" >
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>DMACD2</refname>
    <refpurpose>MACD Difference Indicator without Ratio</refpurpose>
    <refclass>Technical Indicator</refclass>
  </refnamediv>


  <refsect1>
    <title>Description</title>
    
    <remark>TO DO - Compare to DMACD, apropos MACD calculation,
    oscillator TA</remark>

    <!-- Ed. Note: The DMACD2 rate line and the DMACD "Difference Line"
         as rate line both function, essentially, as a "Delayed MACD"
         rate line, but only on non-JPY markets (Peculiar!).

         On the same non-JPY markets, the "DoSMa/Price Ratio" rate
         line - avaialble with the OTILB DOsMA indicator - functions
         as a "Delayed OsMA" rate line.

         The "different beavior" of these indicators on JPY symbols
         should bear some further study.
    --> 
    
    <sidebar>
      <title>Analogous Indicator: CCI</title>
      
      <para>The presentation of the DMACD2 <glossterm>technical
      indicator</glossterm> may resemble, visually, the presentation
      of the Composite Channel Index (CCI) <glossterm>technical
      indicator</glossterm>.</para>
    </sidebar>
    
  </refsect1>
